contemporary claim
Homonym Number:
Word Class:noun
Sense Number:
Definition:a Maori claim on present-day resources, e.g. a share of the radio spectrum
Origin:[none]
Register:
Register 2:
Domain:[none]
Region:[none]
See:
Pronunciation:
Notes: contrastive with historic(al) claim; also as contemporary grievance below
